definitions.definition: To hang or attach to, as by a string, so that the thing is suspended
examples: a seal appended to a record
An inscription was appended to the column.

definitions.definition: To add, as an accessory to the principal thing; to annex
examples: notes appended to a book chapter

definitions.definition: To write more data to the end of a pre-existing file , string , or other object.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To hang or attach to, as by a string, so that the thing is suspended
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To add, as an accessory to the principal thing; to annex
( computing ) To write more data to the end of a pre-existing file , string , or other object.
